{
  "texts": [
    "However, the professional group members' attitude towards the results given by the LLM is because they have more experience than the LLM, so the additional information provided to them by LLM is limited.",
    "Note that the professional group has a positive attitude towards the results of DeGPT compared to the results of the direct decompiler output since even the lowest score reaches 7.",
    "Thirdly, we observe that Q1 possessed lower scores than the other questions in all three groups.",
    "After interviewing the participants, we learn this is mainly because some optimized code has too many detailed comments, more than the programmers would write.",
    "This adds to the burden of reading the code and makes the participants feel that the optimized code is not idiomatic enough compared with the hand-written code."
  ]
}